LIFE SKILL UNLOCKED 

With many YouTube videos and a whole lot more trial and error I have taught myself how to milk a cow! And I also have to mention at the same time I have taught a cow how to be milked! 

Our milking journey didn’t start off how I had planned because her calf was still born…it was the first time this has happened on our farm and after shedding a all the tears I had to just jump right in. No time to dwell. 

Cows, especially when they first come into milk have to be milked everyday or they run the risk of developing mastitis which is an infection in the milk ducts. 

No matter what, everyday she needs to be milked out fully which when I started took me approximately 2 hours. Now thankfully it only takes me about 45 mins hahaha 

The thing I love most about milking a cow is that we feed off each other so much. If I come to her stressed and in a rush she feels that and gets stressed out as well. I have to come to her with love and compassion and I gotta admit being a mom prepared me so much for that 😂

Do you have any questions? I’d love to talk to you guys about this!

It’s truly sad how women are not taught about their bodies. 

Like you can only get pregnant 6 days a month while you’re ovulating. All the other days of the month your vagina is a sperm killing machine. 

You can track your cycle with a basal thermometer and see when youre ovulating, on top of several other signs that tell you. 

Birth control literally mines your body of so many essential nutrients. And if you’re on birth control for a symptom, you’re not treating what youre body is telling you. You’re just shutting down your symptoms and not treating the root cause. 

We used to live in cultures that older women would share this knowledge and tons more but that has been lost. It’s tragic 😣

If youre looking to understand your body more I’d recommend this book called The Fifth Vital Sign. Take your power back 🤘🏼

I know the modern comforts are well….comfortable but at what cost? I’m learning more and more that cost is in fact our health

FARM, FAMILY, RECIPES 

After the post I made yesterday this seemed to be the most wanted thing and honestly that made me extremely happy!! 

While wrestling is a big part of my life my family, farm and food are the MOST important. 

I will start posting more farm content along with how I run our household and of course, some of my favorite recipes and what my family eats. 

I’m very passionate about all these things so be ready for an info dump 😂

WINTER ON THE FARM 

My three main goals for running my farm during the winter is food, water and warmth. 

The cows get hay dropped everyday, the chickens go through about a bag of feed and waters need filled daily. 

In my experience where we live we just have to make sure the wind isn’t effecting the animals to much and their fur/feathers huddled together do the rest. 

So we make sure the cows have trees to stand around and the chicken coop isn’t drafty. 

To keep us warm we have to cut a bunch of fire wood. We’re not nearly as hearty as the rest of the things on our farm 😂

What questions about wintering and keeping critters and peoples warm do you have? 

Drop em in the comments. 

Also shout out to Mama Rowe for the socks and hat 🤘🏼🤘🏼
#VikingRaiders #ivar #Valhalla #tozawa #alphaacademy #wwe #raw #wweraw

75 HARD 

A few weeks ago Ray asked me to join along with me and do the 75 Hard challenge and honestly it’s been great. Showing up for yourself everyday and having discipline is FANTASTIC for mental health and amazing for your body. 

The rules are. 

🐮 Two 45min workouts a day, one must be outside. 
🐮 Daily Progress Photos 
🐮 Drink 1 gallon of water (I do a half gallon for health reasons) 
🐮 10 pages of reading 
🐮 Stick to a diet 
🐮 No cheating for alcohol 

Thanks for asking me to do this Ray, it’s been a pleasure struggling with you ❤️

SWIPE TO THE END FOR THE FUN FACT 

While smashing my head into Maxxine I also smashed my face into her fist and gave myself a fat lip. 

No one kicks my ass like I do!! 😂

MY PURPOSE 

Finding a purpose in life is such a comfort. To know I can’t be replaced brings me a peace and safety that I didn’t know I was living without. 

Being a wife and a mother also has allowed me to be feminine in a way I didn’t think possible for me. It has shown me it’s okay to soften and to become a person that isn’t the same. 

I tell people a lot I’m not longer Sarah, I’m Cash’s mom because that’s how much I have changed! But becoming such a caring mother not only has blessed my family with someone who is caring and nurturing but it has also given me that. 

I’m more patient with myself and I allow myself more grace. I am kinder when I talk to myself and allow for more mistakes. I am happier for myself when small things happen and I allow myself to feel safe in my own presence. 

I had no idea what you were going to turn me into Ray Rowe by making me a wife and a mother but I will spend the rest of my life showing you gratitude for it. 

-With all the love and Peace 
Cash’s Mom ❤️

RECIPE: 🐻BEAR SHOULDER ROAST WITH VEG🐻

Serving Size 3 Rowes 

Pre-heat oven to 450

Put in food processor and handful of garlic cloves, a coating of oregano and a coating of paprika and one stick of melted butter. Blend until married. 

Cut up 3 carrots into circles and add some washed mushrooms and add to the pan. 

Melt a stick of butter and drizzle over vegetables then add garlic powder, oregano, and parsley. Add how much feels right. 

Put roast facedown on veggies and add half the blended seasonings. Flip roast and add the rest. 

Cook at 450F for an hour or until roast is at 165F

***with omnivores especially bears trichinosis can be present so make sure the meat at 165F before eating.

CASH BOY DIET 

He basically eats like a bear 😂

Mostly beef (prefers ground) along with dairy, fruits and veggies. 

I honestly could not pick a better diet I would rather have him on. It warms my heart that he eats the way he does and I wouldn’t change a thing! 

He wasn’t always like this though! For over 2 years he was exclusively breastfed. Not by my choice but he literally wouldn’t eat anything else. And then he would only eat ground beef, rice, and some “healthy” cereals. 

But I was patient and steadfast and just took all the things I didn’t want him to eat out of the house and, of course it helps that we eat the way we want him to eat. 

He doesn’t just eat this way cause he doesn’t like junk, he eats this way because we don’t give him a choice of junkie stuff 😂

I’m one proud mama
